comment:
That has seemed to be pretty clearly the direction things are going with this.  The whole METOO movement IS still valid, but it's gone WAY too far and has often become guilty of the same kind of intimidation and reputation evisceration that men like Harvey Weinstein and his surrogates commited.  In many ways it's WORSE, since public accusations that are untrue against a person who makes a living in the public eye  (like an actor)
can see their entire future burned out forever with no way to really recover.  
I'm a liberal.  But we have investigative legal systems precisely to protect both accused and accuser from unproven and  damaging falsehoods that can subvert the rule of law and the ability of the public to identify, understand, have confidence in and ultimately accept the truth of a thing when it's staring them in the face.   That is why FoxNews, the GOP, and trump are such destructive forces.  Its ALSO why what I've started calling VENDETTA FEMINISM is also so destructive.   It's not just false public accusations and the kind of thing we're seen here in this trial and similar events come up it's also about Hollywood and the way they have treated men and the classic action/scifi/drama franchises that men grew up with and love, myself included.  Its NOT that casting more women is bad.  It's not bad to see more films written, directed, produced, or acted in by women.  The problem is the purposeful, malevolent punch to the face that comes via the REPLACEMENT of lead male characters central to the story, who are iconic and both brilliantly written  with female characters who are purposely written and performed in a way DESIGNED to make men seem innately cruel, stupid, weak, petty, or bumbling-puppylove-dumbnstruck and totally dependent on the somehow brilliant, sarcastic and unquestionably unquestionable female lead to  disrespect the fans fans and the films they love.  That's the VENDETTA.   If your goal is to empower women, to open up the film industry to equality while still making movies people WANT TO SEE, then taking greatly loved films that people grew up loving and twisting them out of shape until the only thing left is a fist giving viewers the finger DOESN'T make a lot of sense.  Nor does doing it in the most clearly male centric, macho genre of ALL: ACTION films.  A genre that is DEFINITELY the most masculine and the one that common-fracking-sense and SALES FIGURES unequivocally demonstrate that this is not a genre that women DO want to see, a genre they DO go see, or a genre they will suddenly, magically want to go see In the future.  So the only reason left is pain.  They are willing to lose MILLIONS of dollars for no reason OTHER than a desire to destroy the things men love to hurt people they hate.  
Behaivor like that in Hollywood has been a political equivalent of a gateway drug that led all too many men down a path of   increasingly inaccurate beliefs that culminated in the modern GOP and voting for Donald Trump.  That trail of destruction has led DIRECTLY from Hollywood to the election of a completely incompetent, sociopathic catastrophe that IS The Trump Administration and finally, because of trumps malevolent vicious incompetence, over 150,000 DEAD Americans Citizens INCLUDING TENS of THOUSANDS of CHILDREN. (SO FAR).

comment:
This is why I just about everybody needs body cameras. Because you know Amber Heard is not the only female who's done this kind of thing to their significant other.

Having the power that your word is presumed to be more honest than another person's when what you say conflicts with what they say has to be corrupting. It has to be tempting. It is the problem when someone vicious isolate someone so they can't defend themselves during the abuse or later in court

We used to presume that people wouldn't lie they took an oath in the Bible. I don't think it was true even then but today, you know police officers and religious figures as well as people who don't believe to begin with lie all the time to get out of trouble. We can't take people at their word anymore if they have any vested interest in the circumstances.
And even third parties can be manipulated into altered memories of events by the right questions and lines of questioning and interrogation.

So that's why we need so many people testifying and even then we still can't be sure. The only way to be sure would be if there was footage of the events.

comment: I originally planned to be a journalist when I left school 20 years ago, it was fine at first but I learned quickly how corrupt it was.  I did a internship/work experience at a local paper and they were publishing my articles with another journalists name whilst that journalist got paid for it and I was getting zero pay and even had to cover my own expenses, I remember covering a court trial and did all the notes for the case and everything and when I submitted my article being told to reword it to make it seem the person accused was guilty as it sells more papers, then a few years later there was a local case for someone I knew who went to court and things were thrown out before it even went to court as it was proven to be wrong, yes it did get brought up in the trial but was thrown out as it was proven wrong, ALL the local papers added it as the truth and didn't mention it was thrown out, the headlines were basically reporting accusations even if they were thrown out straight away, and headlines like "is this person a violent criminal?"  They were trying to influence the trial and didn't care if what they were reporting was the truth, the person who was proven not guilty was attacked in the street various times after the trial and had to move away as people didn't believe he was innocent due to not even the charge at court but because they believed what the paper said which was proven not the be true at court, not just thrown out but PROVEN to be not true.  The local Police force basically shrugged their shoulders and said they were just doing their job, before even that they raided his house and trashed it, breaking furniture etc looking for evidence which they never got which took a whole day to put his home back in one piece, and he never got back personally effects they thought were "relevant" to the case which of course was conveniently his computer, his expensive phone, his STEREO, his branded clothes and left things worth nothing i.e unbranded clothes, old cd's.  Oh and they then "lost" all this afterwards and refused to pay out insurance and said he had to sign a document waiving them of any responsibility.

comment: There is a difference between the court ruling that what the Sun published was untrue and the court finding the Sun and Dan Wootton defamed him and that Depp deserves compensation. If the court finds it is the first case Depp gets nothing except an acknowledgement that the Sun published something untrue. To achieve the second the court has to find that the Sun either knew what they published was untrue or had no reason to believe it was true. The evidence so far is to establish whether Depp was a wife beater. The second half of the trial, if it gets that far, will be about why the Sun and Wootton, if they did at all, believed what they published about Depp.If the Sun got information from Heard either directly or indirectly and it was believed because it was felt to be believable at the time the court can at best make a finding that the belief was wrong. Once that finding is made it becomes a legal fact. The British media can then not repeat the original claim as fact without new evidence and if it is done Depp would be entitled to damages.  Fun can be had on the way if a witness commits perjury or refuses to answer questions. Depp, in his evidence, did not sugar coat his nature and came across as believable and a bit weird. That is the approach Elton John has used in various trials and it tends to work. It will be interesting to see how Heard and her sister present themselves. Heard will get into enormous difficulty if she presents herself as a mouse-like innocent after what has come out so far. A possible successful approach could be "OK, I'm a self-obsessed vile bitch and so what if I drink too much, shat on his bed and had multiple affairs? He was still violent to me." She might not want to do that because of what it could do to her image.  There is fun to come.
